Explanation: 
•	The form helps the user in creating the account. On Submitting the register form, if all the validations return true, then First Name, Last Name, Password, Email, Country, Gender and Date of Birth will be persisted in the Database which results in the successful signup.
•	Using the following details which are persisted in the Database, User can login to the Home Page.
•	There are options for Country and Gender which displays as a Drop Down. The User must select one of them to fill the form or it will set to default value.
•	User can select Date of Birth from the calendar which automates the date in the field.
•	If the user is already registered and have an account, then user can navigate to login page and use their appropriate credentials to navigate to home page.

Server Code Script for Signup:

<?php

include("includes/connection.php");
	if(isset($_POST['sign_up'])){
	$first_name = htmlentities(mysqli_real_escape_string($con,$_POST['first_name']));
	$last_name = htmlentities(mysqli_real_escape_string($con,$_POST['last_name']));
	$pass = htmlentities(mysqli_real_escape_string($con,$_POST['u_pass']));
	$email = htmlentities(mysqli_real_escape_string($con,$_POST['u_email']));
	$country = htmlentities(mysqli_real_escape_string($con,$_POST['u_country']));
	$gender = htmlentities(mysqli_real_escape_string($con,$_POST['u_gender']));
	$birthday = htmlentities(mysqli_real_escape_string($con,$_POST['u_birthday']));
	$status = "verified";
	$posts = "no";
	$newgid = sprintf('%05d', rand(0, 999999));
	$username = strtolower($first_name . "_" . $last_name );
	$check_username_query = "select user_name from users where user_email='$email'";
	$run_username = mysqli_query($con,$check_username_query);
	$check_email = "select * from users where user_email='$email'";
	$run_email = mysqli_query($con,$check_email);
	$check = mysqli_num_rows($run_email);
	if($check==1){
	echo "<script>alert('Email already exist, please try another!')</script>";
	echo "<script>window.open('signup.php','_self')</script>";
	exit();
	}
	$rand = rand(1, 3); //Random number between 1 and 2
		if($rand == 1)
			$profile_pic = "head_red.png";
		else if($rand == 2)
			$profile_pic = "head_sun_flower.png";
		else if($rand == 3)
			$profile_pic = "head_turqoise.png";
	$insert = "insert into users (f_name,l_name,user_name,describe_user,Relationship,user_pass,user_email,user_country,user_gender,user_birthday,user_image,user_cover,user_reg_date,status,posts,recovery_account) values ('$first_name','$last_name','$username',' status.','........','$pass','$email','$country','$gender','$birthday','$profile_pic','default_cover.jpg',NOW(),'$status','$posts','ifyouaregoodatsomethingdontdoitforfree8247306749')";
	$query = mysqli_query($con,$insert);
	if($query){
	echo "<script>alert('Congratulations $first_name, your account has been created successfully.')</script>";
	echo "<script>window.open('signin.php','_self')</script>";
	}
	else {
	echo "<script>alert('Registration failed, try again!')</script>";
	echo "<script>window.open('signup.php','_self')</script>";
	}
}
?>

Explanation:
•	Once User is registered, Connection with Database would be initiated, and queries will run in the backend to fetch the data.
•	Validation for Password will be done based on the script written. If the password length is less than 8 characters, then popup will be displayed saying that “Password should be minimum 8 characters!”
•	When the user tries to register, it checks if the email is already registered. If email already exists, then a popup will be displayed saying that “Email already exists, please try another”. Duplicate data is not encouraged, and validations are done accordingly.
•	Profile picture will be selected randomly for the user based on the script.
•	If the user meets the required conditions, then based on the successful query results the account will be created successfully else would go back to the Signup page saying “Registration failed, try again!”

